history.text: I have not seen this, have you?
Yea I have, a long time ago though.
What did you think of  Ben Affleck?
Ben Affleck was good. It was nice seeing him with Henry Cavill.
These critical responses don't really make me want to see it. lol
Yea, that makes sense. Lex was a really weird villain, especially with Jesse Eisenberg.
I like the description of him there, "with a little bit of Mark Zuckerberg."
I think it's weird to have a movie where two superheros are pinned against eachother.
Yea, I feel like having two superheros go head to head always devolves into a generic slugfest. I'd agree that it was more a "spectacle of power" than anything else.
Do you have a document about another movie? I just have this one.
I just have one too. It says it should change but it hasn't so far.
Nevermind, it just changed.
lol, yeah just then
What do you think about the concept of a Batman who has already been operating in Gotham for two decades?
Yeah, I mean it's kind of his town by that point. But because he's this "vigilante" character, he thinks badly of Superman, I suppose?
Yea, mostly because of how powerful Superman can be if he chose to go bad.
Ah, I see. Yeah and Batman is all gadgets and muscle. I've always kind of liked Batman for those reasons too.
Yea, Batman's always great. Like the reviews said, Nolan's Dark Knight set a pretty high bar.
Yes. Now, I did see that one. I liked it a lot. I didn't really follow the movies much after that.
That's fair. Man of Steel was worse than this and this didn't get that great of a reception.
So spoilers with the document, Batman could have potentially defeated Superman, but his emotional side saves the day. It does seem so ... typical.
Is Superman portrayed as more of a "level head" compared to Batman?
Yea, especially with Luthor manipulating Batman for most of the time.
What do you think of the ending?
It made me laugh kind of. I wasn't expecting Superman to actually die, but then that coffin levitates.
Yea, there was no way they would actually kill Superman. He's way too big of a name
Okay, so Luthor managed to kill Superman?
well "kill" Superman
Yea, in a roundabout way. Mostly through manipulation
Well there's no point of watching this movie now. lol
Excuse my ignorance, but did they release another after this?

Yea, this is only the second movie in 
the DC Extended Universe.
Are there comics of the Extended Universe as well?
I'm not really sure actually.
So do we hit the finish conversation button now since we've seen all four documents?
